# Page skill (pointer)

The canonical, always-current version of this skill lives at [`/skills/page/SKILL.md`](../../skills/page/SKILL.md). Read it in full before acting on a page-level change.

Short summary:

- Stockholm pages always exist as a **Swedish + English pair**. Berlin story pages always exist as a **German + English pair**. Do not edit only one locale unless the user explicitly asks for a single-locale change.
- Adding a page requires changes in `site-html/`, `site/scripts/extract-page-shell-meta.mjs` (`PATH_TO_HTML`), running `npm run page-shell:meta`, then updates to `STOCKHOLM_SV_EN_PAIRS` / `BERLIN_DE_EN_STORY_PAIRS`, `PAGE_CUSTOM_BODY_PATHS`, `[...slug].astro` imports and `pageBodies` map, new body components under `site/src/components/page-bodies/`, and `navigation.ts` entries.
- New photos follow `docs/responsive-image-workflow.md` (three derivatives, correct `SUFFIX`, wired via the documented helper).
- Verify with `npm test && npm run build` from `site/`. If images changed, consider the performance recipe in `/skills/performance-check/SKILL.md`.

See the canonical file for the full workflow (edit / add / rename / remove), files touched, locale parity rules, verification details, escalation triggers, and worked examples.
